Revised autoconfiguration (#16)

- Let the C compiler find the ndbm.h or gdbm.h files
  (instead of looking for them in specific directories).
- Don't use the gdbm-ndbm.h compatibility mode, it no longer exists.

commit.message:
Clean up and modernize the C stubs

Use CAML_NAME_SPACE and caml_ prefixed names.
String_val returns const char * .
Introduce and use alloc_datum and extract_datum convenience functions.

commit.message:
Look for ndbm.h in /usr/local/include too (#2)

In macOS 10.12.4
% brew install gdbm --with-libgdbm-compat
puts ndbm.h in /usr/local/include.
Introduce a compatiblity layer above gdbm when the ndbm interface is not available (#5)

Update info on Debian/Ubuntu packages to install

As reported in #4, Debian is changing the organization of its packages for GDBM.

Closes #4.
Apply patches from OPAM package for v1.0
